http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/Cookery-contest/article13990113.ece

A cookery contest in traditional cuisine is being organised for women as part of the festive season on Monday. Daspalla Hotels, in association with Jain Brothers and Food Craft Institute, Visakhapatnam, is organising the contest – Daspalla Sankranti Vantakalu – to celebrate traditional cooking and to recognise the contribution of traditional food.Winners would be given away prizes at the Sankranti Sambaralu organised at the hotel on January 15, general manager of the hotel S. Prashant said in a statement issued here. For registration and details, call assistant F&B manager Sudhakar Panda on 0891-2564825, 2563141.